## Limitations

The findings are based on available data and reports, which may not capture the full scope of the labor market dynamics. The rapidly changing economic conditions and ongoing impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic mean that the situation is fluid and subject to change. Additionally, the reliance on online sources may introduce biases based on the perspectives and focus areas of the authors. Further research, including primary data collection and longitudinal studies, would provide a more comprehensive understanding of the labor shortage.